1
00:00:13,467 --> 00:00:15,433
Our families are still enemies.

2
00:00:15,500 --> 00:00:19,367
Isn't that enough reason for us
to stop whatever we have?

3
00:00:19,433 --> 00:00:20,933
Why don't we just choose
for ourselves

4
00:00:21,000 --> 00:00:22,800
and not for our families?

5
00:00:22,867 --> 00:00:25,833
I hope our love for each other
overcomes everything.

6
00:00:25,900 --> 00:00:28,133
Sorry, Red, but I don't want us
to ruin our relationship

7
00:00:28,200 --> 00:00:31,067
with our families
by being selfish.

8
00:00:32,267 --> 00:00:33,233
Yen!

9
00:00:35,733 --> 00:00:36,767
It's about Red!

10
00:00:36,833 --> 00:00:38,867
- Something happened to Red.
- What?

11
00:00:38,933 --> 00:00:41,533
He got into an accident
with that girl.

12
00:00:41,600 --> 00:00:43,600
She's at the hospital.

13
00:00:43,667 --> 00:00:44,700
What?

14
00:00:44,767 --> 00:00:45,867
She's at the hospital?

15
00:00:45,933 --> 00:00:47,833
Why? What happened?

16
00:00:47,900 --> 00:00:52,067
Red, I can't forgive myself if
something bad happens to you.

17
00:00:52,133 --> 00:00:54,667
Red, please wake up.

18
00:00:54,733 --> 00:00:56,867
Red, I'm going to talk to you.

19
00:00:56,933 --> 00:01:00,500
No matter how hard
I deny my feelings,

20
00:01:00,567 --> 00:01:04,533
my heart still says I love you
so much.

21
00:01:08,800 --> 00:01:09,967
Really?

22
00:01:10,033 --> 00:01:12,333
Please don't panic,
but something happened to Red.

23
00:01:12,400 --> 00:01:13,633
What happened?

24
00:01:13,700 --> 00:01:14,867
He got into an accident.

25
00:01:14,933 --> 00:01:16,567
He was brought to the hospital.

26
00:01:16,633 --> 00:01:18,233
Which hospital?

27
00:01:21,700 --> 00:01:23,000
You again?

28
00:01:23,067 --> 00:01:25,733
You're the one who keeps
following me.

29
00:01:25,800 --> 00:01:27,733
You're like a magnet.

30
00:01:27,800 --> 00:01:29,100
You stick with me.

31
00:01:29,167 --> 00:01:31,900
You're like a yo-yo. No matter
how often I throw you out,

32
00:01:31,967 --> 00:01:33,067
you keep coming back.

33
00:01:33,133 --> 00:01:36,467
You said you would talk to me
if I woke up.

34
00:01:36,533 --> 00:01:40,067
If it's true that you are here
for your daughter,

35
00:01:40,133 --> 00:01:44,567
I hope she's in a grave
condition.

36
00:01:44,667 --> 00:01:45,767
Aren't you going to stop?

37
00:01:45,833 --> 00:01:47,467
- Oh my God, Auntie!
- Leave my daughter alone!

38
00:01:47,533 --> 00:01:50,267
I will accept every
insult you give me.

39
00:01:50,333 --> 00:01:54,533
But I will never let you do
anything against my daughter!

40
00:01:54,600 --> 00:01:57,033
I won't move until you
talk to me.

41
00:01:57,100 --> 00:01:58,133
Red, get back down!

42
00:01:58,200 --> 00:01:59,367
It's dangerous!

43
00:02:02,733 --> 00:02:04,233
Rina!

44
00:02:04,300 --> 00:02:06,167
Stop!

45
00:02:06,233 --> 00:02:08,467
Stop it, Red! Come on!

46
00:02:08,533 --> 00:02:11,333
I want to be happy because
I listened to my heart.

47
00:02:11,400 --> 00:02:15,600
But is it right to be happy
while our parents are in misery?

48
00:02:15,700 --> 00:02:18,233
We'll find the perfect timing.

49
00:02:18,300 --> 00:02:22,200
Once they've healed, we can tell
them the truth.

50
00:02:27,267 --> 00:02:28,600
I cannot help it, Victor.

51
00:02:28,667 --> 00:02:34,500
My hatred towards Amanda won't
go away just like that.

52
00:02:34,567 --> 00:02:36,200
What do you take me for?

53
00:02:36,267 --> 00:02:37,300
A balloon?

54
00:02:37,367 --> 00:02:40,467
That once you pop,
everything disappears?

55
00:02:40,533 --> 00:02:45,167
Especially now that she's
poisoning Red's mind.

56
00:02:45,233 --> 00:02:46,933
I'd better not say anything,
Rina.

57
00:02:47,000 --> 00:02:48,733
I'm tired.

58
00:02:48,833 --> 00:02:51,333
What matters to me
now is Red's safety.

59
00:02:51,400 --> 00:02:54,667
If something wrong
happened to Red,

60
00:02:54,733 --> 00:02:57,000
that would be Amanda's fault.

61
00:02:57,067 --> 00:02:59,033
Red and I had an argument
because of that woman!

62
00:02:59,100 --> 00:03:00,500
Because Amanda...

63
00:03:00,567 --> 00:03:02,633
That's enough!

64
00:03:02,700 --> 00:03:05,267
If someone is at fault here,
it's you!

65
00:03:05,333 --> 00:03:11,067
If you only left Amanda alone,
our son wouldn't have seen her!

66
00:03:11,133 --> 00:03:13,133
She wouldn't have come near Red
to make us look bad!

67
00:03:13,200 --> 00:03:14,133
This is your fault!

68
00:03:14,200 --> 00:03:16,733
No, it's not, Victor!

69
00:03:16,800 --> 00:03:18,733
Take back what you said!

70
00:03:18,800 --> 00:03:19,967
I'm leaving.

71
00:03:20,033 --> 00:03:23,200
I'm going to find Red
before he totally disappears.

72
00:03:25,900 --> 00:03:27,433
Gosh!

73
00:03:27,500 --> 00:03:30,467
Rina's always asking
for trouble!

74
00:03:30,533 --> 00:03:33,700
She doesn't want to stop
bothering me.

75
00:03:33,767 --> 00:03:36,967
But I won't back down!

76
00:03:37,033 --> 00:03:40,933
You went there for Eden,
but you saw someone else.

77
00:03:41,000 --> 00:03:43,500
You didn't see Eden, Auntie?

78
00:03:43,567 --> 00:03:44,533
No.

79
00:03:44,600 --> 00:03:45,667
She's not there.

80
00:03:47,867 --> 00:03:50,367
Eden!

81
00:03:50,433 --> 00:03:51,633
What hurts?

82
00:03:51,700 --> 00:03:52,933
What happened to you?

83
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:55,233
What happened to you?

84
00:03:55,333 --> 00:03:56,800
Which hospital did you go to?

85
00:03:56,867 --> 00:03:58,867
I went to the hospital
Raichu told me about,

86
00:03:58,933 --> 00:04:00,533
but you weren't there.

87
00:04:00,600 --> 00:04:01,833
I'm okay, Mom.

88
00:04:01,900 --> 00:04:04,700
I just accompanied a friend.

89
00:04:04,767 --> 00:04:06,567
That's right, Auntie.

90
00:04:06,633 --> 00:04:07,833
Friend.

91
00:04:07,900 --> 00:04:09,267
You were in a hurry.

92
00:04:09,333 --> 00:04:11,633
I wasn't finished talking
yet when you left.

93
00:04:11,700 --> 00:04:13,367
Who is that friend?

94
00:04:13,433 --> 00:04:15,233
Our friend...

95
00:04:15,300 --> 00:04:19,000
from swimming. Yes, swimming.
She's our teammate.

96
00:04:19,067 --> 00:04:22,700
Your friend from
the swimming team?

97
00:04:22,767 --> 00:04:23,933
Yes.

98
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:26,267
Why did you have to keep it
from me?

99
00:04:26,333 --> 00:04:30,100
And why did Raichu have to lie
that you were in a meeting?

100
00:04:30,200 --> 00:04:31,767
What?

101
00:04:35,333 --> 00:04:36,767
It's okay, Amanda.
Let's just forget about it.

102
00:04:36,833 --> 00:04:42,067
Nothing wrong happened
to Eden anyway.

103
00:04:42,133 --> 00:04:44,400
I'm sorry, I panicked.

104
00:04:44,467 --> 00:04:46,100
I got scared.

105
00:04:46,167 --> 00:04:51,000
I don't know what to do
if something happens to you.

106
00:04:51,067 --> 00:04:52,433
I have little savings.

107
00:04:52,500 --> 00:04:53,967
I'll buy a cell phone.

108
00:04:54,033 --> 00:04:56,833
So I can call you, okay?

109
00:04:58,567 --> 00:05:00,133
I'm sorry, Mom.

110
00:05:09,400 --> 00:05:11,367
Where's my phone?
Can I have my phone?

111
00:05:14,233 --> 00:05:15,300
Here.

112
00:05:21,600 --> 00:05:22,667
Pick up.

113
00:05:26,667 --> 00:05:27,633
He's not answering.

114
00:05:27,700 --> 00:05:30,133
He's not answering my calls!

115
00:05:30,200 --> 00:05:32,233
Where's Red?

116
00:05:32,300 --> 00:05:35,300
If Red was brought
to a different hospital,

117
00:05:35,400 --> 00:05:40,400
I think it was Yenyen's
decision.

118
00:05:40,467 --> 00:05:41,433
What made you say so?

119
00:05:41,500 --> 00:05:42,900
How would you know?

120
00:05:42,967 --> 00:05:47,867
The students who saw
the incident said

121
00:05:47,933 --> 00:05:51,067
he was with Yenyen when it
happened.

122
00:05:51,133 --> 00:05:55,733
Honestly, Yenyen is a bad
influence on Red.

123
00:05:55,800 --> 00:05:59,933
Red often got harmed when
we were on the island

124
00:06:00,000 --> 00:06:03,633
because of Yenyen.

125
00:06:03,700 --> 00:06:06,733
I'm curious about Yenyen.

126
00:06:06,800 --> 00:06:09,600
I want to meet her.

127
00:06:09,700 --> 00:06:12,100
Auntie, she's a nobody.

128
00:06:12,167 --> 00:06:15,300
That's why I won't be surprised
if, one day,

129
00:06:15,367 --> 00:06:18,067
she'll use Red
to have a better life.

130
00:06:19,167 --> 00:06:25,567
Then why does Red love
that Yenyen so much?

131
00:06:25,633 --> 00:06:27,500
I don't know, Auntie.

132
00:06:27,567 --> 00:06:30,767
I don't know what Red
saw in her.

133
00:06:30,833 --> 00:06:33,733
Suddenly he's into her.

134
00:06:33,800 --> 00:06:37,367
He's even neglecting his school
and other stuff

135
00:06:37,433 --> 00:06:39,467
because of that woman.

136
00:06:44,467 --> 00:06:46,667
- Red! Red!
- Red.

137
00:06:46,733 --> 00:06:48,400
What happened to you?

138
00:06:48,467 --> 00:06:50,833
Where did you get that wound?

139
00:06:50,900 --> 00:06:51,933
It's nothing, Mom.

140
00:06:52,000 --> 00:06:54,667
This isn't serious.

141
00:06:54,733 --> 00:06:56,633
You got me worried, Red.

142
00:06:56,700 --> 00:06:59,567
I know we had an argument
earlier on.

143
00:06:59,633 --> 00:07:00,900
I'm really sorry.

144
00:07:00,967 --> 00:07:03,433
I'm sorry, Son.

145
00:07:03,500 --> 00:07:05,667
No, Mom. I am sorry.

146
00:07:05,733 --> 00:07:07,933
I shouldn't have talked back.

147
00:07:08,000 --> 00:07:10,233
Sorry, I'm just confused.

148
00:07:10,300 --> 00:07:15,533
Don't worry. From now on, I will
stay out of my brother's case.

149
00:07:15,633 --> 00:07:18,900
I heard you were with Yenyen
when this happened.

150
00:07:18,967 --> 00:07:20,233
Look.

151
00:07:20,300 --> 00:07:24,000
I don't want to start anything
that we'll argue about.

152
00:07:24,067 --> 00:07:28,100
But according to what Sabina
told me,

153
00:07:28,167 --> 00:07:31,500
Yenyen isn't a good influence
on you.

154
00:07:35,400 --> 00:07:40,567
Starting today, we decided
to end things.

155
00:07:40,633 --> 00:07:43,500
We decided to part ways
and avoid each other.

156
00:07:44,900 --> 00:07:47,367
You don't have to worry
about that anymore.

157
00:07:58,533 --> 00:08:01,733
I was so nervous yesterday
because of what happened.

158
00:08:01,800 --> 00:08:04,333
Your mom almost caught you.

159
00:08:04,400 --> 00:08:08,167
Can you just avoid Red
next time?

160
00:08:08,233 --> 00:08:09,933
I'm sorry, Auntie.

161
00:08:10,000 --> 00:08:12,767
I can't do that anymore.

162
00:08:12,833 --> 00:08:14,400
How come?

163
00:08:14,467 --> 00:08:18,967
Red and I got back together.

164
00:08:19,033 --> 00:08:19,967
Oh my God!

165
00:08:20,033 --> 00:08:21,900
Do you know what you got
yourself into?

166
00:08:22,000 --> 00:08:25,300
Your mom will get mad once
she finds out about it.

167
00:08:25,367 --> 00:08:28,167
You know about your situation,
don't you?

168
00:08:28,233 --> 00:08:30,167
I tried to avoid him, Auntie.

169
00:08:30,233 --> 00:08:33,333
But he keeps coming back to me.

170
00:08:33,400 --> 00:08:37,533
And he told me that her mom paid
someone off to expedite

171
00:08:37,600 --> 00:08:39,100
my mom's case.

172
00:08:39,167 --> 00:08:43,000
So he's now convinced
that my mom is innocent.

173
00:08:43,067 --> 00:08:45,267
Is that the reason you got
back together?

174
00:08:45,333 --> 00:08:46,567
- No.
- Then what?

175
00:08:46,633 --> 00:08:47,933
I love Red.

176
00:08:48,000 --> 00:08:49,567
That's why I went back to him.

177
00:08:49,633 --> 00:08:51,567
I can't leave him.

178
00:08:54,500 --> 00:08:59,267
What you want is impossible.
I don't think our families

179
00:08:59,367 --> 00:09:01,233
will reconcile. You and Red.

180
00:09:01,300 --> 00:09:03,100
And your mom and Rina.

181
00:09:03,167 --> 00:09:05,800
It's the same as saying Ukraine
and Russia will reconcile.

182
00:09:05,867 --> 00:09:07,467
Let's go.

183
00:09:07,533 --> 00:09:09,633
- Hey! Wait!
- Mom?

184
00:09:09,700 --> 00:09:10,600
I'm glad I caught you.

185
00:09:10,667 --> 00:09:12,633
- What's that?
- That's for you.

186
00:09:15,433 --> 00:09:16,633
Cell phone?

187
00:09:16,700 --> 00:09:17,667
What?

188
00:09:17,733 --> 00:09:19,633
This is just an expense.

189
00:09:19,700 --> 00:09:23,267
It doesn't matter how I got it.

190
00:09:23,333 --> 00:09:25,867
I won't worry anymore.

191
00:09:25,933 --> 00:09:27,500
You need that.

192
00:09:27,600 --> 00:09:32,200
I can call you, and you can
call me anytime, right?

193
00:09:32,267 --> 00:09:34,567
You need that.

194
00:09:34,633 --> 00:09:37,400
Thank you, Mom.

195
00:09:37,467 --> 00:09:39,100
You're the best.

196
00:09:39,167 --> 00:09:41,167
You're the best too.

197
00:09:41,233 --> 00:09:42,300
Wow! She has a new cell phone!

198
00:09:42,367 --> 00:09:44,533
Make sure you use it, okay?

199
00:09:53,033 --> 00:09:54,967
Sabina's here.

200
00:09:55,033 --> 00:09:57,133
She'll tell on us.
I'll go ahead.

201
00:10:08,233 --> 00:10:09,733
Hi, Red!

202
00:10:15,733 --> 00:10:20,133
Why were you talking to Yenyen?

203
00:10:20,200 --> 00:10:23,767
It's nothing. She just asked me
something.

204
00:10:23,833 --> 00:10:26,733
Are you sure?

205
00:10:26,800 --> 00:10:32,000
And is it true that you're going
to avoid her?

206
00:10:32,067 --> 00:10:37,167
You heard me last night.

207
00:10:37,267 --> 00:10:40,533
Well, then...

208
00:10:40,600 --> 00:10:42,233
Maybe we can still work on...

209
00:10:42,300 --> 00:10:43,600
Sab.

210
00:10:43,667 --> 00:10:46,900
Stop right there, Sab.

211
00:10:46,967 --> 00:10:48,833
If you think that just because
me and Yeynyen broke up

212
00:10:48,900 --> 00:10:51,533
we can easily go back
to how we were,

213
00:10:51,600 --> 00:10:53,233
you're wrong.

214
00:10:53,300 --> 00:10:54,667
We can only be friends.

215
00:10:57,100 --> 00:11:04,400
Why is it so easy for you
to give me up?

216
00:11:04,467 --> 00:11:06,000
You don't even want
to give me a chance

217
00:11:06,067 --> 00:11:09,733
to improve myself for you.

218
00:11:09,833 --> 00:11:12,300
Because our relationship
is impossible.

219
00:11:12,367 --> 00:11:13,933
We really are not compatible.

220
00:11:15,967 --> 00:11:17,133
And last night,

221
00:11:17,200 --> 00:11:20,433
I know you're ruining Yenyen's
reputation with my mom.

222
00:11:20,500 --> 00:11:23,267
Well, you don't have to do that
anymore.

223
00:11:23,333 --> 00:11:25,400
Because we're over.

224
00:11:30,733 --> 00:11:32,233
Red.

225
00:11:45,700 --> 00:11:48,167
OMG, Friend!

226
00:11:48,233 --> 00:11:50,100
I knew you couldn't just ignore
Red.

227
00:11:50,167 --> 00:11:56,233
Family issues have no match
with Red's charm.

228
00:11:56,300 --> 00:11:59,133
Recycled lover.

229
00:11:59,200 --> 00:12:07,167
When love is biodegradable,
we can easily recycle it.

230
00:12:07,233 --> 00:12:08,600
I have a hashtag for you.

231
00:12:08,667 --> 00:12:11,100
#ReDenAgain!

232
00:12:11,167 --> 00:12:12,300
You're so loud!

233
00:12:12,367 --> 00:12:13,633
I told you it's a secret.

234
00:12:13,700 --> 00:12:15,100
You're so stubborn.

235
00:12:15,200 --> 00:12:18,400
Make sure you hold your tongue
when my mom is there.

236
00:12:18,467 --> 00:12:20,300
I'm telling you.

237
00:12:20,367 --> 00:12:23,733
Well, that's the problem.

238
00:12:23,800 --> 00:12:27,067
I'm happy whenever I'm with Red.

239
00:12:27,133 --> 00:12:31,700
But sometimes, when we're
together, I think of my mom.

240
00:12:31,767 --> 00:12:36,367
I wonder what her reaction
will be if she sees me

241
00:12:36,433 --> 00:12:41,367
with the son of the woman
who sent her to jail.

242
00:12:41,433 --> 00:12:43,000
You know what?

243
00:12:43,067 --> 00:12:44,933
I couldn't look my mom
in the eye last night.

244
00:12:45,000 --> 00:12:49,100
I was afraid she'd know
I was lying.

245
00:12:49,200 --> 00:12:52,700
You really are in a difficult
situation.

246
00:12:52,767 --> 00:12:54,167
You didn't choose one.

247
00:12:54,233 --> 00:12:56,100
You chose all of the above.

248
00:12:56,167 --> 00:12:57,433
I love it.

249
00:13:02,367 --> 00:13:04,900
Am I selfish?

250
00:13:04,967 --> 00:13:09,900
I chose my happiness over
my mom's feelings.

251
00:13:09,967 --> 00:13:15,600
Eden, it's not wrong
to be happy.

252
00:13:15,667 --> 00:13:20,033
It's okay as long as you don't
hurt or trample anyone.

253
00:13:20,100 --> 00:13:26,100
But in your case, it's like
choosing the one you love more.

254
00:13:26,200 --> 00:13:28,667
Is it your mother or Red?

255
00:13:28,733 --> 00:13:31,267
Can't I choose both?

256
00:13:31,333 --> 00:13:32,267
I love my mom.

257
00:13:32,333 --> 00:13:34,000
That's why I don't want her
to get hurt.

258
00:13:34,067 --> 00:13:35,000
I also love Red.

259
00:13:35,067 --> 00:13:37,133
That's why I don't want
to let him go.

260
00:13:37,200 --> 00:13:39,067
I love them both.

261
00:13:39,133 --> 00:13:42,167
So maybe we'll just take a risk.

262
00:13:42,233 --> 00:13:46,633
And hope that our families'
situation will change.

263
00:13:46,700 --> 00:13:47,667
I'll tweet that.

264
00:13:47,733 --> 00:13:50,100
Your quotes are lovely.

265
00:13:50,167 --> 00:13:52,167
I love Mom. I don't want her
to get hurt.

266
00:13:52,233 --> 00:13:54,000
I love Red. I don't want
to let him go.

267
00:13:54,067 --> 00:13:55,067
Beautiful.

268
00:13:55,167 --> 00:13:56,100
Stop it.

269
00:13:56,167 --> 00:14:00,067
That's so beautiful.
I'll tweet it.

270
00:14:00,133 --> 00:14:01,700
It might go viral.

271
00:14:05,967 --> 00:14:07,233
Yenyen.

272
00:14:09,967 --> 00:14:11,867
Can I talk to you for a moment?

273
00:14:13,433 --> 00:14:15,833
I saw you earlier with Red.

274
00:14:15,900 --> 00:14:19,500
When you told me that you'd stay
away from him.

275
00:14:19,567 --> 00:14:20,900
So what is it like that?

276
00:14:20,967 --> 00:14:23,600
Why do you keep chasing him?

277
00:14:23,667 --> 00:14:26,800
Sabina, I don't have to explain
myself to you.

278
00:14:26,867 --> 00:14:30,633
I only came here because I
needed to retrieve some stuff.

279
00:14:30,733 --> 00:14:32,667
So please just leave me alone.

280
00:14:34,167 --> 00:14:39,200
Why don't you just admit
that you keep chasing Red?

281
00:14:39,267 --> 00:14:41,867
That you still want to get back
with him.

282
00:14:41,933 --> 00:14:43,167
Well, guess what?

283
00:14:43,233 --> 00:14:46,500
He told me he'd stay away
from you.

284
00:14:46,567 --> 00:14:50,233
So if I were you,
I would stop too.

285
00:14:50,300 --> 00:14:52,400
He can avoid me.

286
00:14:52,467 --> 00:14:54,200
There's no problem with that.

287
00:14:54,267 --> 00:14:57,000
What are you so mad about?

288
00:14:57,067 --> 00:14:58,700
Let me guess...

289
00:14:58,767 --> 00:15:01,933
You're being like that because
even if Red and I are over,

290
00:15:02,033 --> 00:15:04,900
he's still not coming back
to you.

291
00:15:04,967 --> 00:15:08,100
You're pushing yourself
to him again.

292
00:15:08,167 --> 00:15:10,100
You're making yourself
look like a fool again.

293
00:15:10,167 --> 00:15:12,367
The nerve to call me a fool.

294
00:15:12,433 --> 00:15:15,033
When I am one of the honor
students on campus.

295
00:15:15,100 --> 00:15:18,133
While you are just good
at swimming.

296
00:15:18,200 --> 00:15:20,933
Truth hurts, isn't it?

297
00:15:21,000 --> 00:15:25,133
Sabina, haven't you learned
your lesson yet?

298
00:15:25,200 --> 00:15:28,100
You're doing it again and again.

299
00:15:28,167 --> 00:15:30,400
Just a reality check, Sabina.

300
00:15:34,400 --> 00:15:37,533
How dare you!

301
00:15:50,133 --> 00:15:52,467
How dare you!

302
00:16:03,433 --> 00:16:04,367
Yenyen.

303
00:16:04,433 --> 00:16:05,767
Oh my God, Yenyen!

304
00:16:05,833 --> 00:16:07,267
- Yenyen.
- Are you okay?

305
00:16:07,333 --> 00:16:09,167
What happened? Oh, no!

306
00:16:09,267 --> 00:16:11,133
Sab, what is it this time?

307
00:16:11,200 --> 00:16:12,567
What? I didn't do anything.

308
00:16:12,633 --> 00:16:14,633
The balls fell on their own.

309
00:16:14,700 --> 00:16:17,400
She's just dumb.

310
00:16:17,467 --> 00:16:19,600
Are you okay?

311
00:16:19,667 --> 00:16:20,933
I'll help you.

312
00:16:21,000 --> 00:16:22,500
My foot hurts, Red.

313
00:16:42,933 --> 00:16:44,667
It doesn't hurt that much now.

314
00:16:44,733 --> 00:16:47,967
That's okay. Someone might
see us.

315
00:16:48,033 --> 00:16:50,367
Don't worry if someone sees us.

316
00:16:50,433 --> 00:16:54,933
I can't just leave you
like that.

317
00:16:55,000 --> 00:16:56,467
Thank you.

318
00:17:55,533 --> 00:17:57,100
Surprise!

319
00:17:57,167 --> 00:17:59,367
Buffet!

320
00:17:59,433 --> 00:18:01,467
There.

321
00:18:04,367 --> 00:18:05,733
Yummy!

322
00:18:07,267 --> 00:18:10,700
This is one of the moments
that I'd like to return

323
00:18:10,767 --> 00:18:13,733
to the island.

324
00:18:13,800 --> 00:18:17,400
I realized we have more freedom
there.

325
00:18:17,467 --> 00:18:19,033
I thought everything
would be okay

326
00:18:19,100 --> 00:18:20,767
when we're back to Manila.

327
00:18:22,533 --> 00:18:26,267
But it's like we're imprisoned
in our families' past.

328
00:18:27,433 --> 00:18:30,633
We have freedom on the island.

329
00:18:30,700 --> 00:18:33,000
We're free to love.

330
00:18:38,100 --> 00:18:45,567
If I am given a chance to return
to that island, I'll do it...

331
00:18:45,633 --> 00:18:47,733
as long as you're with me.

332
00:19:23,967 --> 00:19:25,700
You shouldn't have brought me
home.

333
00:19:25,767 --> 00:19:27,600
What if my mom sees you?

334
00:19:27,667 --> 00:19:30,567
Come on. It's okay. I can't let
you go home on your own.

335
00:19:30,667 --> 00:19:33,300
My foot is okay now.
And I can handle myself.

336
00:19:33,367 --> 00:19:36,200
Actually, you can drop me off
here.

337
00:19:36,267 --> 00:19:38,200
People might see us.

338
00:19:38,267 --> 00:19:39,633
Bye.

339
00:19:40,767 --> 00:19:41,967
Be safe.

340
00:19:42,033 --> 00:19:43,433
Be safe.

341
00:20:01,800 --> 00:20:02,867
Yen!

342
00:20:06,567 --> 00:20:08,700
You forgot your phone.

343
00:20:08,767 --> 00:20:10,267
You shouldn't have
handed it to me.

344
00:20:10,333 --> 00:20:12,567
My mom might see you.

345
00:20:12,633 --> 00:20:22,600
Okay. I'll go ahead.

346
00:20:23,900 --> 00:20:25,200
Hey.

347
00:20:25,267 --> 00:20:25,933
Mom.

348
00:20:26,000 --> 00:20:28,600
What are you doing here outside?

349
00:20:28,667 --> 00:20:31,933
Eden and I almost came
at the same time.

350
00:20:32,000 --> 00:20:34,900
There's a neighbor
who chatted with me.

351
00:20:35,000 --> 00:20:36,700
That's why I stayed here a bit.

352
00:20:46,467 --> 00:20:47,567
Eden!

353
00:20:47,633 --> 00:20:49,367
Eden! Your mom is coming!

354
00:20:49,433 --> 00:20:51,067
She'll see Red!

355
00:20:51,133 --> 00:20:53,333
- You should hide!
- Hide! Hurry!

356
00:20:56,000 --> 00:20:58,833
Whose car is that?

357
00:20:58,900 --> 00:21:02,100
Our neighbor has a wealthy
suitor.

358
00:21:02,167 --> 00:21:03,533
Amazing, right?

359
00:21:03,600 --> 00:21:05,033
It's so flashy.

360
00:21:05,100 --> 00:21:07,367
Come on, let's cook.

361
00:21:07,433 --> 00:21:10,167
Our neighbor is unbelievable.

362
00:21:43,033 --> 00:21:47,167
Dindi, can you take care
of the dishes?

363
00:21:47,233 --> 00:21:48,867
I woke up early this morning.

364
00:21:48,933 --> 00:21:50,300
- Sure.
- I'll get some rest now.

365
00:21:50,367 --> 00:21:53,667
- I got this.
- Okay, thank you.

366
00:21:53,733 --> 00:21:55,133
Eden, good night.

367
00:21:55,200 --> 00:21:57,533
Good night, Mom.

368
00:22:16,667 --> 00:22:23,567
Eden, I've been lying a lot to
your mom just to protect you.

369
00:22:23,633 --> 00:22:26,000
Honestly, I'm scared
that Amanda will find out

370
00:22:26,067 --> 00:22:29,433
I'm lying to her too.

371
00:22:29,500 --> 00:22:34,033
Auntie, I'm not ready
to tell her yet.

372
00:22:34,100 --> 00:22:39,100
And Red and I promised
that we would tell our parents

373
00:22:39,167 --> 00:22:41,733
at the right time.

374
00:22:41,800 --> 00:22:43,833
What if they find out
about it first?

375
00:22:43,900 --> 00:22:47,567
What if they catch the two of
you before you can tell them?

376
00:22:55,733 --> 00:22:59,867
It's okay to tell her
about it yourself.

377
00:22:59,933 --> 00:23:03,033
I know your mother cannot
accept that right away.

378
00:23:03,100 --> 00:23:09,000
But she will get hurt more if
she finds out from someone else.

379
00:23:09,067 --> 00:23:12,700
If I were you, I'd stop before
it's too late...

380
00:23:12,767 --> 00:23:15,867
if you can't commit to it.

381
00:23:30,767 --> 00:23:32,667
Do you want to meet tomorrow?

382
00:23:32,733 --> 00:23:34,933
Let's talk about
what we should do.

383
00:23:35,000 --> 00:23:38,533
Okay. See you.

384
00:23:38,600 --> 00:23:41,033
Mom, I'm going out.

385
00:23:41,100 --> 00:23:42,933
I have to go somewhere.

386
00:23:43,000 --> 00:23:44,767
It's Saturday.
Where are you going?

387
00:23:44,833 --> 00:23:48,033
Raichu asked me to go with her
to buy swimwear.

388
00:23:48,100 --> 00:23:50,300
Follow that taxi.

389
00:23:50,367 --> 00:23:52,133
Is it something like a date?

390
00:23:52,200 --> 00:23:53,600
Are they on a date?

391
00:23:53,667 --> 00:23:54,600
Yes, Auntie.

392
00:23:54,667 --> 00:23:56,133
Why don't you come here?

393
00:23:56,233 --> 00:23:59,933
So that once and for all,
you're going to meet Yenyen.

394
00:24:00,000 --> 00:24:02,267
I'm looking forward
to meeting her, really.

395
00:24:02,333 --> 00:24:04,967
I want to know who Yenyen
really is.

396
00:24:05,033 --> 00:24:06,400
Mom, what are you doing here?

397
00:24:06,467 --> 00:24:08,567
I'm here to meet Yenyen.

398
00:24:10,633 --> 00:24:12,267
Eden?
